description.p:
It can also be graded using modified criteria which better fit with clinical practice (Porta C et al. Clin Exp Med 2007, 7:12-134):



    

1. numbness, dysaesthesia, paraesthesia, tingling, painless swelling, erythema or discomfort of hands or feet, which does not disrupt patient's normal activities;

2. One or more of the following symptoms: painful erythema, swelling, hyperkeratosis of the hands or feet, discomfort affecting the patient's normal activities;

3. One or more of the following symptoms: moist desquamation, ulceration, blistering, hyperkeratosis, severe pain of the hands and feet, severe discomfort that causes the patient to be unable to work or perform daily activities.
